In article <55500@cup.portal.com> ts@cup.portal.com (Tim W Smith) writes:
>One thing I've seen that can be real annoying to crack is to have most
>of the code encrypted.  When the program loads, the non-encrypted part
>computes the decryption key.

Not a big problem, just use a debugger and interrupt the programme after
it loads.  I've used this serveral times on executables compressed with
programmes like PKLite.

